cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with reinforcement learning, specifically exploring sparse reward environments using intrinsic motivation. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new type of intrinsic reward that takes into account statistics over complete trajectories, which involves analyzing visual inputs (cs.CV). The use of hierarchical intrinsic drives also suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE).
